<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="frequently_asked_questions"></span>Frequently Asked Questions<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1761988177760"><strong class="schema-faq-question">How long does it keep?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Refrigerate in an airtight container or jar in the fridge for up to 2 days. Shake or toss before serving.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1761988217992"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Can I use pre-shredded carrots?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Absolutely, just make sure they’re fresh for the best texture.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1761988231717"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Can I use frozen or cooked carrots?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">You wouldn&#8217;t get the signature crunch with cooked carrots, but you can still enjoy the dressing on those.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1761988422700"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Can I adjust the spice level?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Of course! Reduce or omit the chili flakes for a milder version, or add more for extra heat.</p> </div> </div>
</div></div>



